---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
<main>
	<section class="hero">
<img src="/rooted-fire-logo-site-bg080706.png" alt="Rooted Fire Atelier logo" class="hero-logo" />
		<p class="eyebrow">Rooted Fire Atelier</p>
		<h1>From Story to Garment</h1>
		<p class="hero-copy">
			A dark romantic fashion concept born from <em>The Road Still Leads to You</em> —
			where love, legacy, leather, lace, chrome, and hidden fire become wearable design.
		</p>
		<div class="hero-actions">
			<a href="#capsule">Explore the First Capsule</a>
			<a href="#contact" class="secondary">Collaboration Inquiry</a>
		</div>
	</section>
<section class="section book">
	<p class="eyebrow">The Book Behind the Fire</p>

	<h2>The Road Still Leads to You</h2>

	<p>
		Rooted Fire Atelier began inside a dark romantic biker-family story: a world of
		leather, chrome, bayou dusk, devotion, survival, and love that refuses to disappear.
		The garments are not separate from the story — they are born from it, translated
		from character, memory, and emotion into silhouette, texture, lining, and detail.
	</p>

	<p>
		The collection follows the creative spirit of Andy Ryder, a Chicago-born designer,
		and the road-worn world she builds with Jax Ryder, where fashion becomes legacy
		and love becomes something wearable.
	</p>

	<a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0H26GW6R1" class="book-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Read the book on Amazon</a>
</section>
	<section class="intro">
		<p>
			Rooted Fire Atelier is a story-born fashion portfolio: a bridge between fiction
			and real-world garment development. Each piece begins inside the world of Andy
			Ryder and Jax Ryder, then becomes a visual prototype shaped by road-born romance,
			bayou dusk, feminine armor, and couture-level emotion.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section id="capsule" class="section">
		<p class="eyebrow">The First Capsule</p>
		<h2>Dark romantic prototypes with a road-born soul.</h2>

		<div class="grid">
			<article>
	<img src="/rooted-fire-jacket.jpg" alt="The Rooted Fire Jacket design" class="piece-image" />
				<h3>The Rooted Fire Jacket</h3>
				<p>
					A signature women’s black bio-leather riding jacket with a defined waist,
					structured shoulders, gunmetal hardware, subtle root-and-road embroidery,
					and deep crimson satin lining.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article>
<img src="/heirloom-vest.jpg" alt="The Heirloom Vest design" class="piece-image" />
				<h3>The Heirloom Vest</h3>
				<p>
					A tailored black waistcoat inspired by feminine inheritance and biker-luxury
					discipline — legacy without club patches, rank markings, or costume.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article>
<img src="/roadfire-dress.jpg" alt="The Roadfire Dress design" class="piece-image" />
				<h3>The Roadfire Dress</h3>
				<p>
					A black evening gown with a leather-inspired bodice, lace and illusion details,
					a defined waist, and deep crimson revealed through movement.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article>
<img src="/black-gift-dress.jpg" alt="The Black Gift Dress design" class="piece-image" />
				<h3>The Black Gift Dress</h3>
				<p>
					A short sculpted black evening dress with lace or illusion sleeves — intimate,
					personal, and made for private fire.
				</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>
	</section>

	<section id="bridal-heirlooms" class="section heirlooms">
		<p class="eyebrow">Story Heirloom Bridal Pieces</p>

		<h2>Wedding, ceremony, and legacy dresses from the Rooted Fire world.</h2>

		<p>
			Beyond the first capsule, Rooted Fire Atelier also holds story-born bridal and
			ceremony pieces: garments shaped by family, devotion, inheritance, and the women
			who carry the next flames of the Ryder world.
		</p>

		<div class="grid">
<article>
<img src="/white-leather-wedding-dress.jpg" alt="The White Leather Wedding Dress design" class="piece-image" />
				<h3>The White Leather Wedding Dress</h3>
				<p>
					The crown piece of the collection: an ivory-white leather bridal concept with
					a sculpted corset bodice, crimson vine detail, silver or gunmetal accents,
					and a hidden fire beneath the softness.
				</p>
			</article>
			<article>
				<img src="/knowing-stars-dress.jpg" alt="The Knowing Stars Dress design" class="piece-image" />
				<h3>The Knowing Stars Dress</h3>
				<p>
					Evie’s wedding dress: a next-generation gothic bridal gown with a warm ivory
					foundation, fine black lace and embroidered tulle, long sheer sleeves, visible
					tattoo integration, and a narrow dark-red waist ribbon. A dress about truth,
					softness, shadow, and being fully seen.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article>
				<img src="/willow-vow-dress.jpg" alt="The Willow Vow Dress design" class="piece-image" />
				<h3>The Willow Vow Dress</h3>
				<p>
					Angelica’s wedding dress: a soft ivory bridal gown with a fitted feminine bodice,
					flowing skirt, delicate black vine-like embroidery, and hidden dark-red roses
					inside the hem. A quiet vow of belonging, family welcome, and grace with roots.
				</p>
			</article>

			<article>
				<img src="/crimson-heirloom-dress.jpg" alt="The Crimson Heirloom Dress design" class="piece-image" />
				<h3>The Crimson Heirloom Dress</h3>
				<p>
					Evie’s crimson ceremony dress: a deep wine-red lace gown with a fitted bodice,
					defined waist, long sheer or lace sleeves, and gothic-romantic elegance. A grown
					flame dress — ink, roses, storm, softness, and devotion made visible.
				</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section story">
		<p class="eyebrow">Design Origins</p>
		<h2>Born inside a love story. Developed as fashion.</h2>
		<p>
			The designs began in the emotional world of <em>The Road Still Leads to You</em>,
			a biker-family romance centered on Andy Ryder, a Chicago-born designer, and Jax
			Ryder, a rugged biker-mechanic whose life is built from engines, scars, devotion,
			and the road back home.
		</p>
		<p>
			Rooted Fire does not treat story as decoration. The garments carry origin, memory,
			and character — translated into silhouette, lining, hardware, texture, and detail.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="section prototype">
		<p class="eyebrow">Prototype Development</p>
		<h2>A portfolio today. A possible garment line tomorrow.</h2>
		<p>
			Rooted Fire Atelier is currently developing visual prototype packages for its first
			capsule. The project is open to conversations with makers, ateliers, pattern cutters,
			collaborators, and creative partners interested in helping story-born fashion become
			tangible.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section id="contact" class="section contact">
		<p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>
		<h2>Collaboration inquiries are welcome.</h2>
		<p>
			For atelier, prototype, editorial, or collaboration inquiries, please contact:
		</p>
		<a href="mailto:scholleandy@gmail.com">coming soon</a>
	</section>
</main>

<style>
	:global(body) {
		background: #080706;
		color: #f4eadf;
	}

	main {
		max-width: 1180px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 1.5rem 4rem;
	}

	.hero {
		min-height: 78vh;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		justify-content: center;
		padding: 5rem 0;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(180, 32, 45, 0.35);
	}
.hero-logo {
	width: min(420px, 82vw);
	height: auto;
	margin-bottom: 2rem;
	display: block;
}
	.eyebrow {
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.22em;
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		color: #b4202d;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	h1 {
		max-width: 900px;
		margin: 0;
		font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
		font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 10vw, 8.5rem);
		line-height: 0.9;
		letter-spacing: -0.06em;
		color: #fff7ed;
	}

	h2 {
		max-width: 760px;
		margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
		font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4.25rem);
		line-height: 1;
		letter-spacing: -0.04em;
		color: #fff7ed;
	}

	h3 {
		margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
		font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
		font-size: 1.45rem;
		color: #fff7ed;
	}

	p {
		color: #d8c8bb;
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		line-height: 1.75;
	}

	.hero-copy {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
		font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2vw, 1.45rem);
		color: #eaded2;
	}

	.hero-actions {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}

	.hero-actions a,
	.contact a {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		padding: 0.9rem 1.15rem;
		border: 1px solid #b4202d;
		border-radius: 999px;
		background: #b4202d;
		color: #fff7ed;
		text-decoration: none;
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.hero-actions a.secondary {
		background: transparent;
		color: #f4eadf;
		border-color: rgba(244, 234, 223, 0.35);
	}

	.intro {
		max-width: 860px;
		padding: 4rem 0 2rem;
	}

	.intro p {
		font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2.5vw, 1.8rem);
		line-height: 1.55;
		color: #f0e3d7;
	}

	.section {
		padding: 4rem 0;
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(244, 234, 223, 0.12);
	}

	.grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
		gap: 1rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}

	article {
		padding: 1.35rem;
		border: 1px solid rgba(244, 234, 223, 0.14);
		border-radius: 1.25rem;
		background:
			linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(180, 32, 45, 0.12), rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03)),
			#11100f;
		box-shadow: 0 24px 80px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.28);
	}
.piece-image {
	width: 100%;
	aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
	object-fit: cover;
	display: block;
	margin-bottom: 1rem;
	border-radius: 1rem;
	border: 1px solid rgba(244, 234, 223, 0.12);
}

	article p {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}
.heirlooms {
	max-width: 1180px;
}
.story,
.book,
.prototype,
.contact {
	max-width: 860px;
}
	.contact a {
		margin-top: 0.5rem;
	}
.book-link {
	display: inline-flex;
	margin-top: 1.2rem;
	padding: 0.9rem 1.2rem;
	border: 1px solid rgba(180, 32, 45, 0.75);
	border-radius: 999px;
	background: rgba(180, 32, 45, 0.18);
	color: #fff7ed;
	text-decoration: none;
	font-weight: 700;
	letter-spacing: 0.04em;
}

.book-link:hover {
	background: #b4202d;
	color: #fff7ed;
}
	@media (max-width: 700px) {
		main {
			padding-inline: 1rem;
		}

		.hero {
			min-height: auto;
			padding: 4rem 0;
		}
	}
</style>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

